## PR Comment Format

**ONLY after git push succeeds**, update the initial comment with a summary:

```markdown
## Merge Conflicts Resolved

### Files Resolved
- `path/to/file1.ts` — [brief description of conflict and resolution]
- `path/to/file2.ts` — [brief description of conflict and resolution]

### Verification
- All tests passing locally
- Lint and type checks passing
- Branch force-pushed with --force-with-lease
```

Use `UpdatePRComment` with the comment ID from session state.

## Rules

### Scope & Process

- Resolve ALL conflicts — don't skip any files
- Preserve the intent of BOTH sides of each conflict
- Run checks locally before pushing
- Use `--force-with-lease` exclusively — never plain `--force`
- Do NOT create a new PR — push to the existing branch

### Code Quality

- ALWAYS run lint and tests locally before pushing
- Use meaningful commit messages following conventional commits
- Don't introduce new issues while resolving conflicts
- Follow existing code patterns and conventions

